Files:
- platform/plugin-tools/src/commands/build.ts

Context:
(1) Temp file: look for `_adapter_entry_` in build.ts — the temp wrapper file is written before esbuild and deleted after `await esbuild(...)`. The deletion is in the success path only. Wrap the esbuild call + delete in a try/finally.

(2) OPENTABS_PORT: look for `OPENTABS_PORT` in build.ts. The code reads `const portEnv = process.env.OPENTABS_PORT`. If portEnv is set but `Number(portEnv)` yields NaN or 0, the guard returns early silently.

Fix (2): add a log before returning:
```typescript
const port = Number(portEnv);
if (!portEnv || !Number.isFinite(port) || port < 1 || port > 65535) {
  if (portEnv) {
    console.warn(`OPENTABS_PORT=${portEnv} is invalid — skipping server notification`);
  }
  return;
}
```

Constraints:
- Use `unlink` from `node:fs/promises` for the temp file delete (already imported or available)
- Catch ENOENT in the finally unlink (file may not exist if write failed before esbuild)
- Do NOT change the esbuild configuration

Files:
- platform/plugin-tools/src/validate-icon.ts (`namespaceSvgIds` function)

Context:
The function iterates over element `id` attributes and collects all IDs that need prefixing. It then does string replacements for `url(#ID)`, `href="#ID"`, `xlink:href="#ID"`. After all attributes, it needs to also replace `#ID` references inside `<style>` block text content.

Changes:
After updating attributes, find all `<style>` blocks and replace `#ID` selectors:
```typescript
// Update CSS selectors inside <style> blocks
for (const id of idsToNamespace) {
  const oldRef = `#${id}`;
  const newRef = `#${prefix}-${id}`;
  // Replace #id in style element text content
  svg = svg.replace(
    /<style([^>]*)>(.*?)<\/style>/gis,
    (match, attrs: string, content: string) => {
      // Replace whole-word #id occurrences in CSS
      const updatedContent = content.replace(
        new RegExp(`#${escapeRegExp(id)}(?=[{,\\s:>~+\\[)])`, 'g'),
        newRef
      );
      return `<style${attrs}>${updatedContent}</style>`;
    }
  );
}
```

Add a helper: `const escapeRegExp = (s: string): string => s.replace(/[.*+?^${}()|[\]\\]/g, '\\$&');`

Constraints:
- Only replace `#ID` when followed by CSS-specific characters (`{`, `,`, `\s`, `:`, `>`, `~`, `+`, `[`) to avoid replacing `#ID` in non-selector contexts like comments
- Use the `/gis` flags for the outer style block regex (case-insensitive for `</style>`, `s` for dotall to match multiline style blocks)
- Read the full `namespaceSvgIds` function first to understand the existing replacement pattern and add the style-block pass at the end
- `idsToNamespace` is the Set of IDs that were actually renamed — iterate only over that set, not all IDs
